                <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Atilius <expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> Glabrio <lb n="2"/>IIIIvir <expan><abbr>quinq</abbr><ex>uennalis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ectus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>fabr</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>delat</abbr><ex cert="low">us</ex></expan> a co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ule</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>praef</abbr><ex>ectus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>cohor</abbr><ex>tis</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><expan><abbr>corum</abbr><ex cert="low"/></expan> <expan><abbr>sagittar</abbr><ex>iorum</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>Titia</abbr><ex cert="low"/></expan> <expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilia</ex></expan> minore natus
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Z. 4: statt [---]corum auch [---]gorum möglich. C. Atilius Glabrio hat nach etruskischer Sitte den Namen der Mutter an seine Nomenklatur angehängt: Titia A.f. minore natus. (B): ILS, ILLRP: Z. 2: fabr[um]; Z. 3: cohor[tis]; CIL XI, ILS, ILLRP: Z. 4: Tyriorum; Dondin, Saddington: Z. 5: E(?)[---]m(?).</p>
